8:46 AM Attorney Drew Lehman in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Uriah Lee Oliver in court, in custody.  Attorney Joseph Corcoran in court for Uriah Lee Oliver. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: Motion to amend the information filed by the State yesterday. Arguments heard; Attorney Corcoran objects to the amendments and moves to dismiss count 4 in the amended information. Court allows the amended information for reasons set forth on the record. Discussion held on the certified documents the State plans on submitting into evidence. Attorney Corcoran objects to the use of these documents. arguments placed on the record. Court finds that the certified copies of the documents from other counties are admissible. Motions in Limine filed by the State. Attorney Corcoran does not object, but requests that the shackles be removed from the DE's hands so he may assist in his own defense; Court grants the request. 
Testimony taken from A.C. (witness granted use immunity from the State), KSD Dep. N. Brooks, KSD Dep. J. Wilson. Victim A.C. is called back to testify regarding the limited questions as discussed discussed by the parties. Court breaks for lunch at 11:43 AM. Parties to return at 1:15 pm.

Case recalled at 1:19 PM. Appearances are the same. The State rests. DE waives his right to testify. Defense rests. Closing arguments heard. Court finds Defendant guilty of counts 1-3 and 6-9. Court does not find the Defendant guilty of counts 4-5. Presentence Investigation ordered. Bond revoked. Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 2:30 pm.
Motion to Amend Information

9:06 AM Attorney Drew Lehman in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Uriah Lee Oliver in court, in custody.  Attorney Joseph Corcoran in court for Uriah Lee Oliver. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: DE waives his right to a jury trial and requests a bench trial. The State does not object. Bench trial will start tomorrow as that is the date witnesses were subpoenaed for. Motions in Limine and the issue regarding certified bail bond copies/court records to be addressed tomorrow morning.
Court trial scheduled for September 27, 2022 at 08:30 am.
